# tina4-ruby — Cursor Rules

Tina4 Ruby v3.10.44. 54 built-in features, zero external dependencies. Ruby 3.0+.

## Key Patterns

```ruby
require "tina4"

Tina4::Router.get "/api/users" do |request, response|
  response.json({ users: [] })
end

Tina4::Router.post("/api/public") { |req, res|
  res.json({ open: true })
}.no_auth
```

## Critical Rules

- Route params use `{id}` not `:id`
- POST/PUT/DELETE require auth by default — chain `.no_auth` to make public
- GET is public by default — chain `.secure` to protect
- ORM uses `to_h` for hash conversion
- Queue job payload: `job.payload` not `job.data`
- Namespace: `Tina4::` — e.g., `Tina4::Router`, `Tina4::ORM`, `Tina4::Auth`
- Methods use snake_case: `get_token`, `hash_password`, `dead_letters`
- Templates are Twig syntax (not ERB)
- Default port: 7147
- Entry point: `Tina4.initialize!(__dir__); Tina4::WebServer.new(app, port: 7147).start`

## Project Structure

Routes in `src/routes/`, ORM in `src/orm/`, templates in `src/templates/`, static in `src/public/`.

See llms.txt for complete API reference.
